snippet: In its second year, the much-maligned HealthCare.gov website showed a vastly improved performance.
abstract: Health Sec Sylvia Mathews Burwell reports that nearly 2.5 million people signed up for health insurance plans through the federal marketplace HealthCare.gov during first four weeks of open enrollment, with one million of those enrolling in one week starting Dec 6.
lead_paragraph: In its second year, the much-maligned HealthCare.gov website showed a vastly improved performance.
